{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ac48172f-5df6-40b1-a606-682da680b047","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll provide the configuration directly based on .NET NativeAOT crash dump mechanics.\n\nHere's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT:\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enable dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t` | Dump path template (`%p`=PID, `%t`=timestamp) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | Custom createdump location |\n\n**Pod spec changes** — `createdump` uses `ptrace`, so the container needs `SYS_PTRACE`, plus a volume for the dumps:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: my-nativeaot-app\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: app\n      image: my-app:latest\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is mandatory — `createdump` uses `ptrace()` to snapshot the process; without it, dump collection silently fails.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is needed because NativeAOT doesn't bundle `createdump` and won't find it at the default CoreCLR runtime path.\n- **Dump type 4 (Full)** gives you the complete memory image for debugging NativeAOT; use type 2 (Heap) if storage is a concern.\n- Consider adding `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` temporarily if you need to troubleshoot the dump collection itself.\n- Size the `emptyDir` to at least your app's working set — full dumps can be large.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e71b47c3-9ed1-4a67-9dd3-3f6338deb490","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and there's no repository to explore. The user is asking for general guidance on configuring automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app in Kubernetes. Let me provide the configuration based on my knowledge.\n\nFor NativeAOT .NET apps, crash dump collection works differently than regular CoreCLR apps:\n\n1. For NativeAOT, the `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` environment variable doesn't work the same way as in CoreCLR. NativeAOT doesn't have the same built-in crash dump infrastructure.\n\n2. For NativeAOT apps, you need to use OS-level mechanisms or configure `createdump` differently.\n\n\nActually, I need to correct that. Starting with .NET 8, NativeAOT gained support for crash dumps through environment variables, so by .NET 11 this should be well-established. The key variables are `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` to enable dumps on crash, and `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` to control the dump type (mini, heap, triage, or full).\n\nFor Kubernetes deployments specifically, there are several infrastructure requirements I need to account for: the container needs `SYS_PTRACE` capability since `createdump` relies on ptrace syscalls, core dump file size limits have to be configured with `ulimit`, and the system's core dump pattern in `/proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern` matters. I also need to ensure there's a volume mounted for storing the dump files and that the `createdump` tool path is properly specified.\n\nSetting up the environment variables to enable mini dumps with the full dump type, configuring the dump output path to a mounted volume, and pointing to the custom `createdump` location. The Pod spec needs the `SYS_PTRACE` capability added, an emptyDir volume for the dumps, and potentially `shareProcessNamespace` enabled depending on the setup. For NativeAOT in .NET 8 and later, the application itself needs to be compiled with crash dump support enabled.","outputTokens":1530,"requestId":"981C:371ABE:752F1B1:81EC80A:69F4064E"},"id":"24ef2340-9f13-4a64-985a-fb1d390b0f51","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:48:25.969Z","parentId":"e0a72568-83d4-442a-9521-3cc4eb61a207"}
